# Temporary and planning files

**Do not** create temporary files, planning documents, or scratch docs (e.g. analysis docs, recovery plans, session notes) in the project root or in any directory that Eleventy builds from (e.g. `./`, `posts/`). They can be accidentally committed and will be rendered into `_site/`.

**Do** place them in **`.cursor/scratch/`** (or another path listed in `.gitignore` and excluded from Eleventy). That folder is ignored by git and by the build, so it will not be committed or published.

Examples of files that belong in `.cursor/scratch/`:
- DELETED-CHANGES-ANALYSIS.md and similar recovery/planning docs
- One-off notes or drafts used only for a session
- Any markdown or text file created to work through a plan with the user

If you create a new temporary or planning document, create it under `.cursor/scratch/` and tell the user where it is.
